---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Work — Lenny Chen">
  <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[var(--color-heading)]">Work</h1>
  <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed">
    Below you can find samples of my work. Most of these are writing samples presented in PDF form, but some are docs tooling work I did that are still live on the web. 
  </p>
  <div class="mt-6 flex flex-col gap-3">
    <a href="/samples/edge-deployment-cycle.pdf" download class="text-[var(--color-heading)] hover:text-[var(--color-link)] transition-colors">
      Edge Deployment Lifecycle <span class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-secondary)]">— Here I explain Palette Edge's deployment lifecycle, illustrated with diagrams made in Excalidraw. </span>
    </a>
    <a href="/samples/trusted-boot.pdf" download class="text-[var(--color-heading)] hover:text-[var(--color-link)] transition-colors">
      Trusted Boot Keys <span class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-secondary)]">— How Spectro Cloud Palette's Trusted Book feature works. Here I explain the relationship between the different keys that underpin the security of the system, and how to generate and manage them. </span>
    </a>
    <a href="https://docs.spectrocloud.com/security-bulletins/reports/#palette" download class="text-[var(--color-heading)] hover:text-[var(--color-link)] transition-colors">
      Palette Security Bulletin <span class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-secondary)]">I automated how Spectro Cloud publishes CVEs affecting its releases, saving our compliant teams tens of hours of busywork every week. </span>
    </a>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
